{"pageProps":{"eyebrow":"AgentSight","page":{"layout":"document","title":"AgentSight Quick Start","description":"Install AgentSight, record an agent process, and inspect the session in the local UI.","descriptionIsExcerpt":false,"bodyHtml":"<p>This guide records one local agent process and opens the built-in web UI.</p>\n<h2 id=\"prerequisites\">Prerequisites</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Linux with eBPF support. Kernel 5.x or newer is recommended.</li>\n<li>Root privileges for loading eBPF programs.</li>\n<li>A target process such as <code>claude</code>, <code>node</code>, or <code>python</code>.</li>\n<li>If building from source: Rust, Node.js, clang/LLVM, and libelf development headers.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"install-a-release-binary\">Install a Release Binary</h2>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">wget</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/agentsight/releases/download/v0.1.1/agentsight</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">chmod</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> +x</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> agentsight</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"record-an-agent\">Record an Agent</h2>\n<p>Choose the process command name used by the agent.</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Claude Code.</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">sudo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ./agentsight</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> record</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -c</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> claude</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Gemini CLI often appears as node.</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">sudo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ./agentsight</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> record</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -c</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> node</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Python-based agent applications.</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">sudo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ./agentsight</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> record</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -c</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> python</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>When the agent uses a Node.js binary with statically bundled OpenSSL, pass the binary path explicitly:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">sudo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ./agentsight</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> record</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --binary-path</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> /usr/bin/node</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -c</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> node</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"open-the-ui\">Open the UI</h2>\n<p>After recording starts, open:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"plaintext\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"plaintext\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span>http://127.0.0.1:8080</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>The UI shows the process tree, event timeline, logs, and resource metrics for the captured session.</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-to-check-first\">What to Check First</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Confirm the target process appears in the process tree.</li>\n<li>Inspect child processes and command execution under the agent.</li>\n<li>Open timeline events around each LLM request or tool invocation.</li>\n<li>Use the log view for raw event payloads when debugging parser behavior.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"stop-recording\">Stop Recording</h2>\n<p>Use <code>Ctrl-C</code> in the terminal running AgentSight. If eBPF programs remain attached after an interrupted run, restart AgentSight cleanly or unload stale probes with the project cleanup scripts from the repository.</p>","headings":[{"id":"prerequisites","text":"Prerequisites","depth":2},{"id":"install-a-release-binary","text":"Install a Release Binary","depth":2},{"id":"record-an-agent","text":"Record an Agent","depth":2},{"id":"open-the-ui","text":"Open the UI","depth":2},{"id":"what-to-check-first","text":"What to Check First","depth":2},{"id":"stop-recording","text":"Stop Recording","depth":2}],"sourcePath":"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia.dev/tree/main/docs/agentsight/quickstart.md","metadata":{"updatedAt":"2026-06-02T03:15:25.000Z","createdAt":"2026-06-02T03:15:25.000Z","authors":[{"name":"LinuxDev9002","email":"linuxdev8883@example.com"}]},"path":"/agentsight/quickstart/","alternates":{"en":"/agentsight/quickstart/","zh":"/zh/agentsight/quickstart/"},"continuation":{"index":{"title":"AgentSight","description":"Zero-instrumentation observability for LLM and AI agent behavior with eBPF.","href":"/agentsight/"},"previous":{"title":"AgentSight Operational Notes","description":"Permissions, privacy, supported environments, and deployment guidance for AgentSight.","href":"/agentsight/operational-notes/"},"next":{"title":"AgentSight Troubleshooting","description":"Common fixes for missing events, TLS hook failures, and UI issues.","href":"/agentsight/troubleshooting/"}},"sidebar":[{"title":"AgentSight","items":[{"title":"Overview","href":"/agentsight/"},{"title":"Quick start","href":"/agentsight/quickstart/"},{"title":"Architecture","href":"/agentsight/architecture/"},{"title":"Visualization","href":"/agentsight/visualization/"},{"title":"Operational notes","href":"/agentsight/operational-notes/"},{"title":"Troubleshooting","href":"/agentsight/troubleshooting/"}]}]}},"__N_SSG":true}